                                     HomerS66              Posts: 707  Joined: Sat Oct 25, 2014 4:31 am                       Top                                                             Reply with quote              Re: Bad Review for Milk VR    Postby Someguitarist » Fri Jan 02, 2015 12:18 pm        Honestly, I think Milk VR should be pulled from the Oculus Store. It sets a dangerous precedent for what passes as ''viewable''. The only totally okay video is the ''Recruit'' one (which is pretty good, actually). The next step down is the ''Explore the Citys'' type video, which is almost okay, but the scene constantly switches to something else without so much as a fade between them. The small group of people I''ve shown this app to (about 5 or so) says it is disorienting and makes them sick.Then the worst offenders are the racing/skydiving videos. No ceiling or floor, and the video vaguely wraps around you in some sort of way that doesn''t make sense. God help someone if this is there first experience in the Gear. This is like 40% of the videos, and they are downright unenjoyable.There needs to be *some* curation here.                                          Someguitarist              Posts: 187  Joined: Mon Apr 22, 2013 5:24 pm                       Top                                                             Reply with quote              Re: Bad Review for Milk VR    Postby Yeticrab » Fri Jan 02, 2015 12:37 pm        arnoudh wrote:I think what everybody is in dire need of is higher resolution 360 degree video cameras.Those GoPro and related cameras just are not capable of capturing enough information to be impressive.It''s not the camera, the latest gopro does 4k video, and with their widest lens you''d need 3 images to cover 360 horizontal. That''s 11520x 6480, which is WAY beyond the Note4''s ability to playback at 60fps. All the 360 videos I''ve seen so far have been only 2880x1440, stereo videos are 2048x2048, and highly compressed. The Gear VR display resolution is 1,280 x 1,440 per eye for just 96 degrees of the video; this means that to meet the display capabilities of the Note 4, the video would have to be closer to 5120x5760, (5120x11520 for 3d). Even if the Note4 was powerful enough to playback videos that size at 60fps, the file sizes would be MASSIVE. Reducing compression (increasing file size) will improve things marginally, but the only way to see major improvement would be in the form of a 180 degree videos which would effectively double the resolution by sacrificing the ability to turn around and see behind you (which is more of a novelty than a practical thing when viewing video content IMO). I just don''t see how clear, crisp 360 video is viable on the Note 4. Hopefully someone solves it.Keep in mind that even if the video playback does ultimately meet the resolution capabilities of the device, it would still only be slightly better than a 480p dvd video experience, given the massive size of the virtual display                                          Yeticrab              Posts: 81  Joined: Mon Dec 22, 2014 12:51 pm                       Top                    Display posts from previous: All posts1 day7 days2 weeks1 month3 months6 months1 year   Sort by AuthorPost timeSubject AscendingDescending              Post a reply           15 posts             • Page 1 of 1              Return to “Samsung Gear VR”         Jump to                                 Oculus                    Announcements                    Oculus General Discussion                    Oculus-ready Games and Demos                    Reporting Issues                    The Oculus Lounge                 Mobile                    Samsung Gear VR                    Mobile SDK Development                    Mobile Showcase                 VR Jam                    Mobile VR Jam 2015 Discussion                    VR Jam 2013 (Locked)                 Oculus Share                    Oculus Share General Discussion                 Oculus D