      Is there any reason to spend an extra $100 on the Galaxy S6 edge?         By Chris Smith on April 7, 2015 at 9:45 AM.   Is there any reason to spend an extra $100 on the Galaxy S6 edge?           Samsung’s Galaxy S6 and Galaxy S6 edge are available for preorder in many markets, with some retailers already shipping the devices to early buyers. While the curved version is the more lauded model, Samsung has yet to convince us that curved screens have a purpose, and a new video from Droid-Life seems to indicate that there isn’t much of a reason to pay for the curved version. More ?        No Comments                    Older ArticlesOlder                        Hubs                    Apple                      8 awesome paid iPhone apps on sale for free for a limited time            How to get an Apple Watch near launch day, even if you missed out on preorders                               Android                      One of Android''s most useful apps just got its biggest update yet - here are the details            Amazing iPhone 6 hack brings the Android Lollipop experience to iOS                               Mobile                      This mega-review covers the Galaxy S6, iPhone 6 and every other flagship phone            Verizon tries to convince customers they don''t really want unlimited data                               Business                      Comcast customer had trouble cancelling his service even after his house burned to the ground            Apple employee quits his job, spills dirt on ''what really goes on'' there                                   FOLLOW BGR           Like BGR on Facebook      Follow @BGR on Twitter      BGR on Google Plus      Follow BGR on LinkedIn                         BGR ON TWITTER               Jonathan S. Geller      @boygenius      11 Apr      Current status instagram.com/p/1WTnfcAaaa/                   Zach Epstein      @zacharye      10 Apr      Apple PR is feverishly studying Kindle press releases in preparati